    • Method Detail

      • getInstance

        public static ArchitectureManager getInstance()
        Creates the singleton instance of the architecture manager with the defined desktop configuration. If this class is called for the first time through this method, then the configuration is set to the default; otherwise, the initial configuration provided in getInstance(int,int,int) is used.
        Returns:
        the singleton instance

      • getInstance

        public static ArchitectureManager getInstance​(int desktopWidth,
                                              int desktopHeight,
                                              int frameSize)
        Creates the singleton instance of the architecture manager with a specified desktop configuration. If this class is called for the first time through this method, then the configuration is set to it forever. Subsequent accesses should be made through getInstance(). Calling this one again with different arguments will have no effect.
        Parameters:
        desktopWidth - - the frame width in pixels
        desktopHeight - - the frame height in pixels
        frameSize - - the square size in pixels of the internal frames
        Returns:
        the singleton instance
